			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Sounds like Grade A propaganda to me.  First, there is the bogus term of insourcing. Second the headline pretends that 400k jobs were created in the recent past. The Austin plant that features so prominently in the article is a Texas Instrument plant that TI sold off rather than operate. So the employees that work at that plant probably used to be employed by a US company that decided their lawyers brought in more profit than their manufacturing.
<br />

<br />
Even the last paragraph is pure propaganda. Many US companies moved their headquarters offshore to evade taxes. So companies like Black and Decker (who used to be 100% American) count as a foreign company for these stats. How many of the alleged 6,400,000 workers claimed by the article were added to that column due to the corporation they worked for moving only their HQ offshore? At least half. And the reason that the others work here are due to content labeling and restriction regulations. Why does Honda and Toyota operate assembly plants in the US? Because of content labeling: they want that "made in the USA label."
<br />

<br />
Or maybe it was like a previous company I worked for. Bought out by a British company, now it would be listed in the stats of the con artists that brought you that article as a foreign company, even though my paycheck never changed, nor the name on the letterhead, nor the way folks answered the phone. 
<br />

<br />
States have been offering huge tax rebates and subsidies to companies to move their state for about the last 20 or so years. Like when the Saturn plant was built in TN. The subsidies and rebates offered to that division of GM were greater than any possible income to the county due to wages and taxes that they would see in over 25 years. Sort of like paying $5 for  a $1.50. Things like: <span style="font-style: italic">we'll waive taxes and zoning for the next 25 years, we will build you whatever roads, schools and sewer systems you need just to get you to move here, and we will even throw in $5,000,000 in cash.</span>
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://story.news.yahoo.com/news?tmpl=story&cid=677&ncid=677&e=1&u=/usatoday/20040406/bs_usatoday/workersaskedtotrainforeignreplacements" target="_blank" class="postlink">Try this article instead</a>, it isn't new, nor does it pretend to be.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
